// var =[]87,'Supplication for one afflicted by whisperings in prayer or recitation','Contre la tentation dans la prière et au cours de la récitation du Coran','نماز یا قرآن پڑھتے ہوئے وسوسہ آنے کی دعا','Quran aur namaz mein waswasay se bachao ki dua','Reference: Muslim     4/1729','Reference: Muslim     4/1729','مسلم ۴/۱۷۲۹ من حديث عثمان بن العاص رضي الله عنه وفيه ففعلت ذلك فأذهبه الله عني','Reference: Muslim     4/1729',1,'170');
// var =[]88,'Supplication for one whose affairs have become difficult','Lorsque l''on rencontre une difficulté','مشکل کے وقت کی دعا','Mushkilat ke hal ki dua','Ibn Hibban in his     Sahih (no. 2427), and Ibn As- Sunni (no. 351). Al-Hafidh (Ibn Hajar)     said that this Hadith is authentic. It was also declared authentic by     ''Abdul-Qadir Al-Arna''ut in his checking of An-Nawawi''s Kitabul-Athkarp.     p106','Ibn Hibban in his     Sahih (no. 2427), and Ibn As- Sunni (no. 351). Al-Hafidh (Ibn Hajar)     said that this Hadith is authentic. It was also declared authentic by     ''Abdul-Qadir Al-Arna''ut in his checking of An-Nawawi''s Kitabul-Athkarp.     p106','رواة ابن حبان في صحيحه برقم ۲۴۲۷ (موارد) وابن السني برقم ۳۵۱ وقال الحافظ هذا حديث صحيح وصححه عبد القادر الأرناؤوط في تخريج الأذكار للنووي ص۱۰٦','Ibn Hibban in his     Sahih (no. 2427), and Ibn As- Sunni (no. 351). Al-Hafidh (Ibn Hajar)     said that this Hadith is authentic. It was also declared authentic by     ''Abdul-Qadir Al-Arna''ut in his checking of An-Nawawi''s Kitabul-Athkarp.     p106',1,'171');
// var =[]89,'Upon committing a sin','Lorsque l''on a commis un péché','جس سے گناہ سرزد ہو جائے وہ کیا کہے اور کیا کرے','Gunah kar baithen to kya kahen aur kya karen? ','Abu Dawud 2/86, At-Tirmithi     2/257. Al-Albani graded it authentic in Sahih Abu Dawud 1/283.','Abu Dawud 2/86, At-Tirmithi     2/257. Al-Albani graded it authentic in Sahih Abu Dawud 1/283.','أبو داود ۲/۸٦ والترمذي ۲/۲۵۷ وصححه الألباني في صحيح أبي داود ۱/ ۲۸۳','Abu Dawud 2/86, At-Tirmithi     2/257. Al-Albani graded it authentic in Sahih Abu Dawud 1/283.',1,'172');
// var =[]90,'Supplications for expelling the devil and his whisperings','Ce qui chasse le diable et ses tentations','شیطان اور اسکا وسوسہ دور کرنے والی دعائیں','Shaytan kab bhagta hai? ','[1]Reference: Abu Dawud     1/206, At-Tirmithi. See also Al-Albani, Sahih At-Tirmithi 1/77, and     Surat Al-Mu''minun, 23:98-9. <br>[2]Reference: Muslim     1/291, Al-Bukhari 1/151. <br>[3]Reference: ''Do not     turn your homes into graveyards, surely the Devil flees from the house     in which Surat Al-Baqarah is read,'' Muslim 1/539. The Devil is also     driven out by the invocations for morning and evening, those that are     said before sleeping and upon waking up, those for entering and leaving     the house, including those for entering and leaving the mosque, and by     many other authentic invocations taught to us by the Prophet (SAW) such     as the reading of ''Ayatul-Kursi, (Al-Baqarah 2:255), and the last two ''Ayat     of Surat Al-Baqarah before going to sleep. Whoever says: ''There is none     worthy of worship but Allah alone, Who has no partner, His is the     dominion and His is the praise, and he is Able to do all things,'' one     hundred times, it will be a protection for him from the Devil throughout     the day.''','[1]Reference: Abu Dawud     1/206, At-Tirmithi. See also Al-Albani, Sahih At-Tirmithi 1/77, and     Surat Al-Mu''minun, 23:98-9. <br>[2]Reference: Muslim     1/291, Al-Bukhari 1/151. <br>[3]Reference: ''Do not     turn your homes into graveyards, surely the Devil flees from the house     in which Surat Al-Baqarah is read,'' Muslim 1/539. The Devil is also     driven out by the invocations for morning and evening, those that are     said before sleeping and upon waking up, those for entering and leaving     the house, including those for entering and leaving the mosque, and by     many other authentic invocations taught to us by the Prophet (SAW) such     as the reading of ''Ayatul-Kursi, (Al-Baqarah 2:255), and the last two ''Ayat     of Surat Al-Baqarah before going to sleep. Whoever says: ''There is none     worthy of worship but Allah alone, Who has no partner, His is the     dominion and His is the praise, and he is Able to do all things,'' one     hundred times, it will be a protection for him from the Devil throughout     the day.''','(۱)أبو داود ۱/۲۰٦ والترمذي وانظر صحيح الترمذي ۱/۷۷ وانظر سورة المؤمنون آية ۹۸-۹۹۔ (۲)مسلم ۱/ ۲۹۱ والبخاري ۱/۱۵۱۔ (۳،۴،۵)رواه مسلم ۱/۵۳۹','[1]Reference: Abu Dawud     1/206, At-Tirmithi. See also Al-Albani, Sahih At-Tirmithi 1/77, and     Surat Al-Mu''minun, 23:98-9. <br>[2]Reference: Muslim     1/291, Al-Bukhari 1/151. <br>[3]Reference: ''Do not     turn your homes into graveyards, surely the Devil flees from the house     in which Surat Al-Baqarah is read,'' Muslim 1/539. The Devil is also     driven out by the invocations for morning and evening, those that are     said before sleeping and upon waking up, those for entering and leaving     the house, including those for entering and leaving the mosque, and by     many other authentic invocations taught to us by the Prophet (SAW) such     as the reading of ''Ayatul-Kursi, (Al-Baqarah 2:255), and the last two ''Ayat     of Surat Al-Baqarah before going to sleep. Whoever says: ''There is none     worthy of worship but Allah alone, Who has no partner, His is the     dominion and His is the praise, and he is Able to do all things,'' one     hundred times, it will be a protection for him from the Devil throughout     the day.''',1,'173');
