// var =[]126,'Remembrance said at a sitting or gathering etc.','Ce qui est dit dans une assemblée','مجلس میں کیا کہا جائے','Douran e majlis ki dua','Reference: Sahih Ibn     Majah 2/321. See also Al-Albani, Sahih At-Tirmithi 3/153.','Reference: Sahih Ibn     Majah 2/321. See also Al-Albani, Sahih At-Tirmithi 3/153.','الترمذي وغيره وانظر صحيح الترمذي ۳/۱۵۳ وصحيح ابن ماجه ۲/۳۲۱ ولفظه للترمذي','Reference: Sahih Ibn     Majah 2/321. See also Al-Albani, Sahih At-Tirmithi 3/153.',1,'231');
// var =[]127,'Supplication for the expiation of sins said at the conclusion of a sitting or gathering etc.','L''expiation du verbiage dans une assemblée','کفارہ مجلس کی دعا','Kaffaara e Majlis ki dua','Reference: Abu Dawud,     Ibn Majah, At-Tirmithi and An-Nasa''i. See also Al-Albani, Sahih At-Tirmithi     3/ 153. Aishah (RA) said: ''Allah''s Messenger (SAW) did not sit in a     gathering, and did not recite the Qur''an, and did not perform any prayer     without concluding by saying ... (then she quoted the above).'' This was     reported by An-Nasa''i in ''Amalul-Yawm wal-Laylah (no.308), and Dr.     Farooq Hamadah graded it authentic in his checking of the same book, p.     273. See also Ahmad 6/77','Reference: Abu Dawud,     Ibn Majah, At-Tirmithi and An-Nasa''i. See also Al-Albani, Sahih At-Tirmithi     3/ 153. Aishah (RA) said: ''Allah''s Messenger (SAW) did not sit in a     gathering, and did not recite the Qur''an, and did not perform any prayer     without concluding by saying ... (then she quoted the above).'' This was     reported by An-Nasa''i in ''Amalul-Yawm wal-Laylah (no.308), and Dr.     Farooq Hamadah graded it authentic in his checking of the same book, p.     273. See also Ahmad 6/77',' أخرجه أصحاب السنن وانظر صحيح الترمذي ۳/۱۵۳، وقد ثبت عن عائشة رضي الله عنها قالت :ما جلس رسول الله صلى الله عليه وسلم مجلساً ، ولاتلى قرآناً ، ولا صلاة إلا ختم ذلك بكلمات... الحديث أخرجه النسائي في عمل اليوم والليلة برقم ۳۰۸ ، وأحمد ٦/۷۷ وصححه الدكتور فاروق حمادة في تحقيقه لعمل اليوم والليلة للنسائي ص۲۷۳','Reference: Abu Dawud,     Ibn Majah, At-Tirmithi and An-Nasa''i. See also Al-Albani, Sahih At-Tirmithi     3/ 153. Aishah (RA) said: ''Allah''s Messenger (SAW) did not sit in a     gathering, and did not recite the Qur''an, and did not perform any prayer     without concluding by saying ... (then she quoted the above).'' This was     reported by An-Nasa''i in ''Amalul-Yawm wal-Laylah (no.308), and Dr.     Farooq Hamadah graded it authentic in his checking of the same book, p.     273. See also Ahmad 6/77',1,'232');
// var =[]128,'Returning a supplication of forgiveness','En faveur de celui qui dit ''qu''Allah te pardonne''','اللہ تجھے معاف فرمائے کہنے والے کے لئے دعا','Maghfirat ki dua dainay walay ko kya kaha jaye?','Reference: Ahmad 5/82,     and An-Nasa''i in ''Amalul-Yawm wal-Laylah p. 218, with checking by Dr.     Farooq Hamadah.','Reference: Ahmad 5/82,     and An-Nasa''i in ''Amalul-Yawm wal-Laylah p. 218, with checking by Dr.     Farooq Hamadah.','أحمد ۵/۲۸ والنسائي في عمل اليوم والليلة ص۲۱۸برقم ۴۲۱ تحقيق الدكتور فاروق حمادة','Reference: Ahmad 5/82,     and An-Nasa''i in ''Amalul-Yawm wal-Laylah p. 218, with checking by Dr.     Farooq Hamadah.',1,'233,234');
