// var =[]144,'Remembrance while ascending or descending','Proclamer la grandeur et la gloire d''Allah au cours du voyage','سفر کے دوران تسبیح و تکبیر','Douran e safar tasbeeh o takbir','Reference: Al-Bukhari,     cf. Al-Asqalani, Fathul-Bari 6/135.','Reference: Al-Bukhari,     cf. Al-Asqalani, Fathul-Bari 6/135.','آل۔ بخاری ، آل۔ عسقلانی ، فَطُل۔ بری 6/135','Reference: Al-Bukhari,     cf. Al-Asqalani, Fathul-Bari 6/135.',1,'254,255');
// var =[]145,'Prayer of the traveller as dawn approaches','Du voyageur aux dernières heures de la nuit','مسافر کی دعا جب صبح کرے','Douran safar subah ke waqt ki dua','Reference: Muslim     4/2086, the meaning of sami''a saami''un (who listens has heard) is that     ''a witness has witnessed our praise of Allah due to His blessings and     favor upon us.'' It could also be read samma''a saami''un, in which case it     means ''one who has heard this statement of mine will convey it to     another and he will say it as well.'' This is due to the attention given     to the Thikr (remembrance of Allah) and supplications made during the     early morning hours. The meaning of his saying ''Our Lord, be with us and     bestow Your favor upon us'' is: ''Our Lord, protect us and guard us. Bless     us with Your numerous bounties, and avert from us every evil.'' See An-Nawawi,     Sharh Sahih Muslim 17/39.','Reference: Muslim     4/2086, the meaning of sami''a saami''un (who listens has heard) is that     ''a witness has witnessed our praise of Allah due to His blessings and     favor upon us.'' It could also be read samma''a saami''un, in which case it     means ''one who has heard this statement of mine will convey it to     another and he will say it as well.'' This is due to the attention given     to the Thikr (remembrance of Allah) and supplications made during the     early morning hours. The meaning of his saying ''Our Lord, be with us and     bestow Your favor upon us'' is: ''Our Lord, protect us and guard us. Bless     us with Your numerous bounties, and avert from us every evil.'' See An-Nawawi,     Sharh Sahih Muslim 17/39.','مسلم 4/2086 ، سمع سامعون کے معنی ہیں (جو سنے سنتا ہے) یہ ہے کہ ''ایک گواہ اس کی رحمتوں اور احسانات کی وجہ سے ہمارا اللہ کی حمد کا گواہ ہے۔'' اسے سمع معاذون بھی پڑھا جاسکتا ہے ، اس صورت میں اس کا مطلب یہ ہے کہ ''جس نے میرا یہ بیان سنا ہے وہ اسے دوسرے کو پہنچائے گا اور وہ بھی یہ کہے گا۔'' اس کی وجہ ٹکر (اللہ کی یاد) پر توجہ دی گئی ہے اور صبح کے وقت میں کی جانے والی دعائیں۔ اس کے کہنے کا معنی ''ہمارے پروردگار ، ہمارے ساتھ رہے اور ہم پر اپنا احسان عطا کریں'' یہ ہے: ''اے ہمارے رب ، ہماری حفاظت فرما اور ہماری حفاظت کرو۔ ہمیں اپنے بے شمار فضل و کرم سے نوازا ، اور ہم سے ہر برائی سے باز آجاؤ۔ '' ملاحظہ کریں اننوی ، شرص صحیح مسلم 17/39','Reference: Muslim     4/2086, the meaning of sami''a saami''un (who listens has heard) is that     ''a witness has witnessed our praise of Allah due to His blessings and     favor upon us.'' It could also be read samma''a saami''un, in which case it     means ''one who has heard this statement of mine will convey it to     another and he will say it as well.'' This is due to the attention given     to the Thikr (remembrance of Allah) and supplications made during the     early morning hours. The meaning of his saying ''Our Lord, be with us and     bestow Your favor upon us'' is: ''Our Lord, protect us and guard us. Bless     us with Your numerous bounties, and avert from us every evil.'' See An-Nawawi,     Sharh Sahih Muslim 17/39.',1,'256');
