// var =[214,'The Best Dua for forgiveness - Sayyidul Istaghfar','Dua for forgiveness #1','مغفرت کی دعا (۱)','Sayyidul Istagfar','He (sallallahu alaihi wasallam) said, ‘Whoever says these words during the day, believing in it firmly, and dies on that day before evening comes, he will be one of the people of Paradise. And whoever says it at night, believing firmly in it, and dies before morning comes, he will be one of the people of Paradise.’ [Saheeh al-Bukhaari (6306)]','He (sallallahu alaihi wasallam) said, ‘Whoever says these words during the day, believing in it firmly, and dies on that day before evening comes, he will be one of the people of Paradise. And whoever says it at night, believing firmly in it, and dies before morning comes, he will be one of the people of Paradise.’ [Saheeh al-Bukhaari (6306)]','آپ (صلی اللہ علیہ وآلہ وسلم) نے فرمایا ، ‘جو شخص دن کے وقت یہ الفاظ کہتا ہے ، اس پر مضبوطی سے یقین کرتا ہے اور شام آنے سے پہلے اس دن مر جاتا ہے ، وہ جنت والوں میں سے ہوگا۔ اور جو شخص رات کو یہ کہے ، اس پر بھروسہ رکھے ، اور صبح آنے سے پہلے ہی مر جائے ، وہ جنت والوں میں سے ہوگا۔ ''']'(صحیح البخاری (6306))','He (sallallahu alaihi wasallam) said, ‘Whoever says these words during the day, believing in it firmly, and dies on that day before evening comes, he will be one of the people of Paradise. And whoever says it at night, believing firmly in it, and dies before morning comes, he will be one of the people of Paradise.’ [Saheeh al-Bukhaari (6306)]',0,'348');
// var =[215,'Duas for Forgiveness','Dua for Forgiveness #2','مغفرت کی دعا (۲)','Maghfirat ki dua',replace('[1] A person who says [the words of this dua] even if he has committed sins as much as the the foam of an ocean, still he will be forgiven. [Abu Dawud- 2:85/ Tirmidhi 5:569]\n[2] From Ibn Umar -RadhiAllaahu anhumma- who said:‘We would count that the Messenger of Allaah -sallAllaahu alayhi wa sallam- would say in one sitting one hundred times: [this dua]. [Collected by Abu Dawood, Tirmidhi & authenticated by Albaani in Saheeh Abi Dawood 5/248]','\n',char(10)),replace('[1] A person who says [the words of this dua] even if he has committed sins as much as the the foam of an ocean, still he will be forgiven. [Abu Dawud- 2:85/ Tirmidhi 5:569]\n[2] From Ibn Umar -RadhiAllaahu anhumma- who said:‘We would count that the Messenger of Allaah -sallAllaahu alayhi wa sallam- would say in one sitting one hundred times: [this dua]. [Collected by Abu Dawood, Tirmidhi & authenticated by Albaani in Saheeh Abi Dawood 5/248]','\n',char(10)),replace('[1] جو شخص [اس دعا کے الفاظ] کہتا ہے یہاں تک کہ اگر اس نے کسی سمندر کی جھاگ کی طرح گناہوں کا ارتکاب کیا ہے ، تب بھی اسے معاف کیا جائے گا۔ [ابوداؤد 2: 85 / ترمذی 5: 569]\n[2] ابن عمر رضی اللہ عنہما سے ، جس نے کہا: ‘ہم یہ گنتے کہ اللہ تعالی کے رسول صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم ایک ہی نشست میں سو بار کہتے ہیں: [اس دعا]۔ [ابو داؤد ، ترمذی کے ذریعہ جمع کرا ہوا اور صحیح ابی دائود 5/248 میں البانی کے ذریعہ تصدیق شدہ]','\n',char(10)),replace('[1] A person who says [the words of this dua] even if he has committed sins as much as the the foam of an ocean, still he will be forgiven. [Abu Dawud- 2:85/ Tirmidhi 5:569]\n[2] From Ibn Umar -RadhiAllaahu anhumma- who said:‘We would count that the Messenger of Allaah -sallAllaahu alayhi wa sallam- would say in one sitting one hundred times: [this dua]. [Collected by Abu Dawood, Tirmidhi & authenticated by Albaani in Saheeh Abi Dawood 5/248]','\n',char(10)),0,'349,367');
