      'Morning dua for protection from jinn/shaytan for the entire day [recite 100 times]',
      'It was narrated from Abu Hurayrah that the Messenger of Allaah (peace and blessings of Allaah be upon him) said: “Whoever says [ this dua ] one hundred times in the day, will have a reward equivalent to that of freeing ten slaves, one hundred hasanahs (good deeds) will be recorded for him, and one hundred sayi’ahs (bad deeds) will be erased from his record, and *it will be protection for him from the Shaytaan for that day*, until evening comes. No one could achieve any better than him except the one who does more than he did.” [Ref: narrated by al-Bukhaari, 31119; Muslim, 2691]',
      'It was narrated from Abu Hurayrah that the Messenger of Allaah (peace and blessings of Allaah be upon him) said: “Whoever says [ this dua ] one hundred times in the day, will have a reward equivalent to that of freeing ten slaves, one hundred hasanahs (good deeds) will be recorded for him, and one hundred sayi’ahs (bad deeds) will be erased from his record, and *it will be protection for him from the Shaytaan for that day*, until evening comes. No one could achieve any better than him except the one who does more than he did.” [Ref: narrated by al-Bukhaari, 31119; Muslim, 2691]',
      'سیدنا ابو ہریرہ سے روایت ہے کہ رسول اللہ صلی اللہ علیہ وسلم نے فرمایا: "جو شخص [اس دعا] کو دن میں ایک سو بار کہے تو اس کو دس بندوں کو آزاد کرنے کے برابر اجر ملے گا ، ایک اس کے لئے سو حسنات (نیکیاں) درج کی جائیں گی ، اور اس کے ریکارڈ سے ایک سو ساعی (برے کام) مٹ جائیں گے ، اور شام کے آنے تک یہ اس کے لئے شیطان سے محفوظ رہے گا۔ اس سے بہتر کوئی حاصل نہیں کرسکتا سوائے اس شخص کے جو اس سے زیادہ کام کرے۔ [حوالہ: البخاری نے روایت کیا ، 31119؛ مسلم ، 2691]',
      'It was narrated from Abu Hurayrah that the Messenger of Allaah (peace and blessings of Allaah be upon him) said: “Whoever says [ this dua ] one hundred times in the day, will have a reward equivalent to that of freeing ten slaves, one hundred hasanahs (good deeds) will be recorded for him, and one hundred sayi’ahs (bad deeds) will be erased from his record, and *it will be protection for him from the Shaytaan for that day*, until evening comes. No one could achieve any better than him except the one who does more than he did.” [Ref: narrated by al-Bukhaari, 31119; Muslim, 2691]',
